<p>but not quite up to our country town style.  Villages such as Caestre are very numerous in this part of Flanders, &amp; in size &amp; importance are midway between our small village &amp; country town.  They are not very much larger than our villages but very much busier.<br/>The shops are generally entered by a door from an ordinary passage opposite which is generally another door leading to a room in which one gets refreshments.  These consist of eggs, coffee, bread &amp; butter, biscuits (at ruinous prices) &amp; sometimes tea.  They pay good attention to the coffee &amp; know how to make it, while tea,</p>
